    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-06-11T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-06-11T18:00:00-05:00" n="577"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d577">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">452.11/218: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hammond</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-06-11T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 11, 1929—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>29. Reference Mr. Blake’s letter to you May 15, 1929,<note n="30"
                        xml:id="d577fn30">Not printed; but see despatch No. 392, May 17, 1929, from
                        Tangier, <ref target="#pg_493">p. 493</ref>.</note> and your despatch 1163,
                    February 28, 1929. Department is awaiting offer from Spanish Government to
                    settle Moroccan claims on basis of <hi rend="italic">ad referendum</hi>
                    agreement between Blake and General Jordana. You may discreetly endeavor to
                    expedite action bearing in mind Department’s instruction in its telegram 52,
                    August 9, 1928,<note n="31" xml:id="d577fn31">
                        <ref target="frus1928v03#pg_358">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1928, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">iii</hi>, p. 358</ref>.</note> concerning claims
                    reserved. Report situation by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
